description: Decimal part of cube root of a(n) starts with digit 8.
links: Harvey P. Dale, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
mathematica: cr8Q[n_]:=Module[{rd=RealDigits[Surd[n,3],10,10]},First[Drop[ rd[[1]], rd[[2]]]] == 8]; Select[Range[500],cr8Q] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Nov 27 2014 *)
author: _Patrick De Geest_, Sep 15 1998.
